there's also [pytest.importorskip](https://docs.pytest.org/en/7.1.x/how-to/skipping.html#skipping-on-a-missing-import-dependency). But I would also prefer something like: 

```python
try:
    skip_test = not _check_soft_dependencies(...)
except ImportError:
    skip_test = True

@pytest.mark.skipif(
    skip_test, reason=f"{dependency name} is a soft dependency and is not installed"
)
def test_something():
   ...
```

is that what you had in mind @fkiraly?
